This paper deals with social welfare in matching markets, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also analyzes two matching mechanisms, which involves algorithmic design and optimization (cs.AI). The measures of social welfare used in the paper are based on utility functions, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves analyzing the performance of these mechanisms on different instances, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with allocation and optimization problems, which is a topic in optimization and control (cs.SI).
